   mixing effects, in the pressure range used. Average absolute accuracies
   of the measurements are estimated to +/- 4\% for line intensities and
   self-broadening coefficients and to +/- 13\% for self-shift
   coefficients. The J and K dependences of the self-broadening
   coefficients have been observed and modeled using an empirical
   polynomial expression. The results are compared with previous
   experimental and calculated data. Our absolute line intensities, S-0,
