empirical Hamiltonian modeling, systematic quantum assignments are made for 2047
transitions from eight bands including four inversion-rotation bands (gs, v2, 2v2, and v4)
and four ro-vibrational bands (v2 – gs, 2v2 – v2, v4 – v2, and 2v2 –v4), as well
as covering their ΔK = 3 forbidden transitions. The measured line positions for
the assigned transitions are in an excellent agreement (typically better than 0.001 cm-1)
with the predictions in a wide range of J and K for all the eight bands. The
comparison with the \{HITRAN\} 2012 database is also satisfactory, although
systematic offsets are seen for transitions with high J and K and those from
weak bands. Also we note that out of the 8 bands, the 2v2 – v4 has not been listed
in the \{HITRAN\} 2012 database. Differences of 20\% are seen between our measured
